~ chapter2_star_fragment

Player: Another Star Fragment...
Player: This one feels... calmer.

Star Fragment: Welcome once more, Blessed One.
Star Fragment: I sensed Araw's light the moment you freed them.

Player: Then the Stars truly are connected.

Star Fragment: Though we are scattered,
Star Fragment: our light still finds one another.

Player: Tell me...
Player: Why was your light sealed inside a Manananggal?

Star Fragment: Because peace is easiest to destroy through fear.

Star Fragment: Long ago,
Star Fragment: the Manananggal was nothing more than a tale told beneath moonlit skies.

Star Fragment: A story meant to remind children
Star Fragment: that courage is stronger than fear.

Star Fragment: They twisted that story...
Star Fragment: and turned it into a weapon.

Player: To make people fear magic?

Star Fragment: No.
Star Fragment: To make people fear one another.

Star Fragment: When fear takes root,
Star Fragment: neighbors become strangers.

Star Fragment: Families shut their doors to one another.

Star Fragment: Villages forget what it means to stand together.

Star Fragment: That is how peace is lost.

Player: So every monster they've created...

Player: ...is meant to divide us.

Star Fragment: Yes.

Star Fragment: A divided community  will never hear the songs of the Stars again.

Player: Then we'll give them something stronger than fear.

Star Fragment: Hold fast to that resolve.

Star Fragment: Every Star Fragment you recover
Star Fragment: restores more than our light alone.

Star Fragment: It rekindles the courage
Star Fragment: for others to believe once more.

Player: Then I'll keep going.

Star Fragment: And I shall walk beside you.

Star Fragment: I am Hiraya,
Star Fragment: the Star of Peace.

Star Fragment: May your heart remain steadfast,
Star Fragment: even when fear surrounds you.

=> END